cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with logical formulas and background theories.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the problem of finding an implementation that meets both semantic and syntactic constraints.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper presents a competition aimed at evaluating different synthesis techniques on a comprehensive set of benchmarks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with automated synthesis of programs.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of grammars to specify the allowed set of candidate implementations.
